# skhd hotkey daemon configuration
#
# Yabai bindings were removed when the tiling window manager was pulled out.
# This file now hosts direct app-focus bindings (rcmd-style).
#
# Reference: https://github.com/koekeishiya/skhd
#
# Division of labor across tools:
#   - Rectangle Pro  → window snapping (Ctrl+Opt+Cmd+* family, SizeUp keymap)
#   - skhd (this)    → one keystroke per app via right-cmd (rcmd) + letter
#   - Alfred         → Cmd+Space typed launch / fuzzy search
#   - AltTab         → Opt+Tab window-level switcher with thumbnails
#
# Why right-cmd: macOS apps almost never bind right-cmd as distinct from cmd,
# so it gives us a fresh modifier namespace with zero collisions. `open -a`
# focuses the app if running, launches it otherwise.

# ── Browsers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
rcmd - b : open -a "Brave Browser"
rcmd - s : open -a "Safari"

# ── Terminals / editors ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
rcmd - t : open -a "iTerm"
rcmd - v : open -a "Visual Studio Code"
rcmd - x : open -a "Xcode"

# ── AI / writing ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
rcmd - c : open -a "Claude"
rcmd - n : open -a "Notes"
rcmd - o : open -a "Obsidian"

# ── Comms ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
rcmd - m : open -a "Messages"
rcmd - l : open -a "Slack"
rcmd - z : open -a "zoom.us"

# ── Productivity ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
rcmd - d : open -a "Todoist"
rcmd - f : open -a "Finder"
rcmd - p : open -a "1Password"
rcmd - i : open -a "Linear"

# ── Music / system ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
rcmd - 9 : open -a "Music"
rcmd - 0 : open -a "System Settings"
